modules.description: Provides conversion between units of measurement using defined unit systems, including parsing, scaling, and arithmetic operations on unit-aware values. Operates on custom types representing quantities with associated units, ensuring type-safe calculations. Used to standardize physical measurements in scientific applications, such as converting temperature or pressure values across different scales.

The module provides unit conversion, arithmetic operations (invert, multiply, divide), and validity checks for unit systems, enabling precise manipulation of physical quantities. It works with unit systems and individual units, supporting operations like creating converters and formatting units. Use cases include scientific computing, data normalization, and handling complex unit transformations in applications requiring dimensional analysis.
